<p>
In part, this is due to the “tough on crime” culture of criminal justice in the U.S., wherein individuals receive significantly longer sentences than elsewhere in the world.  On average, individuals convicted of committing fraud serve 10.9 months in jail in England, 30 months in Australia, and 44 months in the U.S..  Likewise, assault charges carry with them, on average, a 15.2 month sentence in England, a 20 month sentence in Australia, and a 60 month sentence in the U.S. 
